// SIGTERM under raw mode (§3 raw-mode safety obligation): enter raw mode, then
// block on a read. The driver sends an EXTERNAL SIGTERM; the safety handler
// installed by enableRaw() restores the terminal (single tcsetattr) and
// re-raises default, so the process dies with a sane terminal — verified by the
// pty driver reading termios back (ICANON/ECHO restored). No signal::on here,
// so SIGTERM is NOT blocked and the handler is what fires.
term::enableRaw();
console.writeln("RAWREADY");
string x = std::sysRead(0, 1);      // blocks in raw mode (VMIN=1) until killed
console.writeln("KEY=" + x);
term::restore();
